  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Prices will drop in a few days",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Commerce Minister Nalin Fernando has said that there will be changes in the retail prices of essential consumer goods in the next few days and the prices of many goods will decrease.",
        "In the last few months, the price of essential commodities has also gone up due to difficulties in importing essential commodities into the country. However, due to the fact that essential commodities are being imported into the country without shortage, the minister said that steps will be taken to reduce the prices of the commodities, and as gas supply has now returned to normal, necessary measures will be taken to control the prices.",
        "Also, people are constantly complaining about the huge increase in the prices of cement, steel bars, wire etc. and the prices of biscuits. Therefore, it has been emphasized that the prices of these products should be considered. They have to visit the consumer authority and declare their price index. He said action will be taken in a few days.",
        "Special attention has been paid to the rising prices of chicken meat and eggs. The Minister has informed the Consumer Protection Authority to investigate and submit a report in this regard."
      ],
